race.comment: ICED POPPY (1) is knocking on the door of that elusive maiden win having placed in her past two, strong to the line at Gundagai two back, close up again at Wangaratta last time. She won't need to improve much at all to be getting the job done here. LADY THINKABELL (3) resumes. Her form in Queensland last time in was solid, just missing fresh at Sunshine Coast. She can measure up. SUPERGRACE (7) has been fair in two runs back but this looks easier and she can be a quick improver. FASTBALL (5) is a filly by Royal Meeting on debut for the Andrew Noblet yard. She's jumped out well and can figure. UNDER CONTROL (9) will find this easier than last time at Sandown HIllside and can bounce back.
